description:
&lt;p&gt;BSUH NHS Trust is looking to recruit a full time outpatient Receptionist to join our busy team in Brighton.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The vacancy is for the following 5 days Monday - Friday 37.5 per week. Hours to be discussed&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;covering over 5 days until 1800hrs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to be confident in your own abilities and able to work under pressure as well as being accurate and numerate and used to working the general public on a face to face basis. Full training will be given.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Flexilbility and to be able to work under own initiatives a key to the role as well as supporting colleagues and management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An apprreciation of the importance of confidentiality is paramount and to be able to demonstrate to others as high level of patient information is available in these areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are hard working , have the ability to work to a high standard, and a good team player and enjoy working with the public, then we would like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Jade Aston&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Operational Manager-Reception&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address j.aston@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01273 696955 ext 2590&lt;/p&gt;
